definitions.definition: An alcoholic beverage made by fermenting grape juice , with an ABV ranging from 5.5–16%.
examples: Wine is usually stronger than beer .
" Wine improves with age but I improve with wine ," she slurred as she slid gracefully beneath the table.

definitions.definition: An alcoholic beverage made by fermenting other substances , producing a similar ABV .
examples: ... dandelion wine , rice wine , plum wine ...
I'd like three beers and two wines , please. My friend will have the same.

definitions.definition: ( uncountable ) The color of red wine , a deep reddish purple .
